{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"petit-cordial-kudu","description":"## Why\nPass-4 coaching (move registry + deterministically rendered notes + guide_url deep-links into docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md) currently runs only over SURVIVING ADVISORY findings (src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py:202, prompt src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_coach.md). Blocking findings - the ones an agent MUST remediate before claim - get no coaching note and no guide_url. Field data: the E6/F1 oracle-strictness finding family recurred 3-5 consecutive rounds on tickets fde0/0ee8/76d2 because agents reworded ACs instead of adding the demanded executable oracle; a guide link plus a move-shaped nudge on the block itself is the cheapest one-round-remediation lever. The reviewer/writer separation must be preserved exactly as-is: moves come from the locked registry, prose is rendered deterministically, the C1 subject validator still rejects code/imperatives/solutions.\n\n## What\n- Extend the Pass-4 coach invocation to also cover blocking findings: same move registry, same subject validator, same deterministic rendering. Implementation seam: the pass-4 call in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py (MOVE_REGISTRY lives there; re-exported by orchestrator.py) - widen the finding set it receives from advisory-only to advisory+block, tagging each coaching note with the finding's decision so consumers can distinguish.\n- Attach guide_url to blocking findings' coaching notes exactly as done for advisories today (orchestrator.py:515-530 passthrough-additive field).\n- CLI: `rebar review-plan` renders the coaching line + guide link for blocking findings the same way it does for advisories (src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py, the existing `-> <coaching> [<link>]` renderer).\n- Sidecar: coaching entries for blocking findings flow through the existing coaching[] persistence unchanged (additive; no schema change).\n\n## Scope\nIN: pass-4 finding-set widening, guide_url attach, CLI rendering, unit tests. OUT: any change to the move registry contents, the subject validator, blocking/advisory decisions, thresholds, or sidecar schema. OUT: conflict-detection between findings (parked epic grumpy-gland-rose).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A plan review whose verdict contains blocking findings emits a coaching entry (move_id + rendered note + guide_url) for each blocking finding. Oracle: new unit test in tests/unit/ asserting coaching coverage over a synthetic verdict with 1 block + 1 advisory yields 2 coaching entries, each carrying guide_url; `python -m pytest tests/unit -k \"coach\" -x` green.\n- [ ] Blocking-finding coaching notes pass the same C1 subject validation as advisory notes (no code, no imperatives). Oracle: existing subject-validator tests extended to a blocking-finding case; suite green.\n- [ ] `rebar review-plan` output for a BLOCK verdict shows the coaching line + guide link under each blocking finding. Oracle: CLI rendering unit test asserting the rendered text contains the guide_url for a blocking finding.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` all pass.","id":"8086-fe2e-c43d-4fb3","parent_id":"d195-aeb8-2400-484b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Extend Pass-4 coaching + guide_url to blocking findings"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784085074112542001,"uuid":"8be8242a-ad01-4839-b469-2c0d3e571f73"}